# Context: a `_gsx` name bound as a FUNCTION-BODY LOCAL — the hole the
# scanner-based checkReservedDecls closes. `_gsxio` shadows the reserved alias
# the generator emits for the "io" import into that same function's render
# closure, so before this pass ran over every Go fragment (not just top-level
# declarations) `gsx generate` exited 0 and the emitted .x.go failed `go build`
# with `"io" imported as _gsxio and not used`. Now it is a clean, positioned
# diagnostic. Pins that the reservation reaches inside a func body, not only
# package scope.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

import "github.com/gsxhq/gsx"

func helper() gsx.Node {
	_gsxio := 4
	_ = _gsxio
	return <b>hi</b>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
6:2: identifier "_gsxio" uses the reserved _gsx prefix (reserved for generated code)
